The Commissioner shall charge:
A fee for the issuance of an initial license under this subtitle in an even-numbered year as follows:
$1,000, if the applicant's annual gross revenue is not more than $3,000,000;
$2,000, if the applicant's annual gross revenue is more than $3,000,000 but not more than $6,000,000;
$4,000, if the applicant's annual gross revenue is more than $6,000,000 but not more than $15,000,000;
$6,000, if the applicant's annual gross revenue is more than $15,000,000 but not more than $30,000,000; or
$8,000, if the applicant's annual gross revenue is more than $30,000,000; and
A fee for the issuance of an initial license under this subtitle in an odd-numbered year as follows:
$500, if the applicant's annual gross revenue is not more than $3,000,000;
$1,000, if the applicant's annual gross revenue is more than $3,000,000 but not more than $6,000,000;
$2,000, if the applicant's annual gross revenue is more than $6,000,000 but not more than $15,000,000;
$3,000, if the applicant's annual gross revenue is more than $15,000,000 but not more than $30,000,000; or
$4,000, if the applicant's annual gross revenue is more than $30,000,000;
A fee for renewal of a license issued under this subtitle as follows:
$1,000, if the applicant's annual gross revenue is not more than $3,000,000;
$2,000, if the applicant's annual gross revenue is more than $3,000,000 but not more than $6,000,000;
$4,000, if the applicant's annual gross revenue is more than $6,000,000 but not more than $15,000,000;
$6,000, if the applicant's annual gross revenue is more than $15,000,000 but not more than $30,000,000; or
$8,000, if the applicant's annual gross revenue is more than $30,000,000;
A fee of $100, for each location in the State at which a licensee provides debt management services under this subtitle, payable at the time of application for an initial license and at each renewal of a license; and
A fee of $1,000, for an investigation of an applicant under this subtitle, payable at the time of application for an initial license.
